<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS; BETTIS CHOOSES WORK ON DAY OFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was players' day off at Rams Park, but running back Jerome Bettis was there 
working hardto build up his battered shoulders. 
</P>
<P>
 "On Mondays I'm usually too sore to get a good workout in and here I am, a 
single guy, 22 years old and what am I going to be doing on an off day?" Bettis 
said."This is better than sleeping until 3. When you have a family, it's 
different. Then I can see where you would be spending time with Junior. 
</P>
<P>
 "Getting these workouts in makes a difference. All that pounding loosens up 
your shoulders, and the stronger you can keep them the better off you're going 
to be." 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Clausen, Ram conditioning coordinator, was wearing one of Bettis' "2,000 
yards or bust" T-shirts. An observer noted that it probably should instead 
read, "1,000 yards if I'mlucky." 
</P>
<P>
 "I knew it would be rough to get 2,000 yards, but that's the goal I set," said 
Bettis, who has gained 814 yards in a league-leading 233 carries. "That's the 
goal I will continue to set, and believe me, I'll get there some day." T.J. 
SIMERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
