<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: FORGET ABOUT OTHERS, LOOK FOR COLD-WATER LUNKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Eastern Sierra trout season has ended, but Southern California's is only 
beginning, as the state is finally beginning to stock local waters with the 
cold-water fish. 
</P>
<P>
 Best bet is Irvine Lake, where a private plant of trophy-sized rainbow and 
German brown trout has anglers supplied with Power Bait pulling out lunkers. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Hernandez of Harbor City took the biggest to date, a 12-pound 8-ounce 
rainbow from the lake's west shore. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona Lake figures to compete, however. Truckloads of trout -- 7,500 pounds 
worth -- will be dumped into the tiny lake this week in preparation for 
Friday's opener. 
</P>
