<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAILY ROUTINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN O. RYAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A typical day for student / working mom Michele Jaimene: 
</P>
<P>
 7 a.m.: Wake up, shower. 
</P>
<P>
 7:15: Wake up 7-year-old Brandon; everyone gets dressed. 
</P>
<P>
 7:45: Breakfast. 
</P>
<P>
 8:10: Take Brandon to school. 
</P>
<P>
 8:45: Take her mother to work. 
</P>
<P>
 9 a.m.-1:30 p.m.: Attend class at Los Angeles City College. 
</P>
<P>
 1:30-5:30: Work at on-campus job. 
</P>
<P>
 6: Pick up Brandon at after-school program. 
</P>
<P>
 6:20: Pick up her mother. 
</P>
<P>
 7: Arrive home. 
</P>
<P>
 7:30: Dinner. 
</P>
<P>
 8-9: Jaimene and Brandon do homework. 
</P>
<P>
 9:30: Lights out for Brandon. 
</P>
<P>
 9:30-11:30: More homework for Jaimene. 
</P>
<P>
 11:45: Lights out for Jaimene. KATHLEEN O. RYAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
