<P>
ROUNDUP; WILSON, GLENDALE WINNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Wilson of Moorpark College posted his sixth victory in seven races this 
season, but Glendale placed five runners among the top seven finishers to 
dominate the team competition of the Western State Conference cross-country 
final Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson, a former standout at Newbury Park High, timed a course record of 19 
minutes 50 seconds over the four-mile distance at Kenneth Hahn Park in West Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson, who set the record of 20:05 in the season-opening Santa Monica 
Invitational, was never seriously challenged. He had a nine-second lead after 
the first mile (4:36) and more than doubled that at the finish. 
</P>
<P>
 Nacho Delgado (20:10), Jacques Sallberg (20:15), Eduardo Macias (20:25) and 
Jose Padilla (20:29) placed second through fifth for Glendale as the Vaqueros 
totaled 21 points to win their sixth WSC title in eight years. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark (76 points), Bakersfield (84), Santa Barbara City (96) and College of 
the Canyons (133) rounded out the top five. GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Village Christian d. Montclair Prep, 15-10, 15-8, 15-11 -- The Crusaders 
rallied from a 10-2 deficit in the first game to win a Southern Section 
Division V wild card match. 
</P>
<P>
 Lindy James had 10 kills and four service aces for Village Christian (10-7). 
Kim McGee and Amy Mikial added six kills each for the Crusaders. Village 
Christian plays Mission Prep on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Bonaventure d. Mayfair, 15-7, 16-14, 16-14 -- Kristin Klarc had 12 kills 
to lead St. Bonaventure (13-4) in a Division IV wild card match at Mayfair. 
</P>
<P>
 Bree Owcraski had 19 assists. WOMENS BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Cuesta d. Moorpark, 15-7, 15-8, 12-15, 9-15, 15-9 -- Dawn Smith had 21 kills 
and Tami Vaillancourt added 18 kills and 21 digs for the Raiders (12-6, 10-3 in 
the Western State Conference). 
</P>
