<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' VOLLEYBALL COACHES STILL IN LIMBO OVER PAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura Unified School District held discussion Tuesday night on a motion 
to pay stipends for boys' volleyball coaches at Buena and Ventura highs, but a 
decision won't be finalized until the next board meeting on Nov. 22. 
</P>
<P>
 The school board currently pays all coaches in all sports except for walk-on 
assistants and boys' volleyball coaches at Buena and Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents and players representing the two teams hoped for a resolution, but 
must meet with the superintendent to clarify questions before the next meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was a little confusion about which budget the money needs to come out 
of -- they thought it was (for) next year, but we want it for the spring." said 
Christine Coil, president of the Buena boys' volleyball booster club. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents originally asked the school district to begin paying stipends in late 
September. 
</P>
<P>
 When the boys' volleyball teams were formed in 1989, the district, citing 
funding shortages, placed the burden of paying the coaches on the parents and 
the players. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents and players raise approximately $5,000 each season for the varsity and 
junior varsity coaches through fund raising. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're going to go ahead and proceed like we've got to raise the funds 
ourselves," Buena Coach Steve Berk said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Prep Sports 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA110994-0091 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 096770 </DOCID>
