<P>
 Comptroller OKs Purchase of Glenfed Branches: Barnett Banks Inc. won approval 
from a second regulator to buy a batch of thrifts, even though the Justice 
Department believes Florida's biggest banking company unfairly denied loans to 
minority borrowers.The Office of the Comptroller of the Currency OKd Barnett's 
plans to acquire 34 Florida branches of California-based Glendale Federal Bank, 
a little more than a month after the Federal Reserve Board granted similar 
approval. The Fed gave its approval while the Justice Department was conducting 
an inquiry of Jacksonville-based Barnett on fair-lending allegations. The OCC, 
which oversees national banks, said it found no evidence of lending bias 
between July, 1993, and July, 1994. 
