<TEXT>
<P>
 Bristol-Myers Squibb Halts Drug Trial: Bristol-Myers Squibb Co. said it halted 
a clinical trial of a heart drug, d-sotalol, after more patients taking the 
drug died than those taking a placebo.The New York-based drug company was 
testing the drug on heart attack victims at risk for cardiac arrhythmia, an 
abnormally fast heartbeat. Bristol-Myers said 54 of 1,373 patients given the 
drug died, compared to 28 of 1,389 placebo patients. The company is continuing 
other clinical trials of the drug. D-sotalol had a market potential of $50 
million, Hemant Shah, an independent analyst in Warren, N.J., said in a 
research report. The company had sales of $11.4 billion last year. 
</P>
