<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; SOUTH AFRICA; BIEHL KILLERS SEEK POLITICAL AMNESTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three young men convicted of murdering California scholar Amy Biehl have begun 
a hunger strike to demand political amnesty, a South African prison official 
said.The students were sentenced Oct. 26 to 18 years in prison. SABC radio said 
the three men -- members of the militant Pan Africanist Student Organization -- 
were refusing to eat and demanding that their crime be seen as political. If 
the men can demonstrate that it was politically motivated and admit their 
guilt, they could qualify for amnesty under a bill now before Parliament. 
</P>
