<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; LAST-PLACE FULLERTON TIES NO. 1 CYPRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton, the Orange Empire Conference's last-place women's soccer team, tied 
Cypress, the top-ranked team in the state, 1-1, Tuesday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second consecutive tie for Cypress (17-0-2, 11-0-2), which had a 
35-game conference winning streak stopped Friday in a 1-1 tie with Palomar. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress outshot Fullerton, 18-2, and took a 1-0 lead in the fifth minute when 
Wendy Pollanzak scored after a corner kick. 
</P>
<P>
 In the 20th minute, Melenee Davidson took a pass from Monica Esparza and 
scored in the upper right corner of the net for Fullerton (3-10-2, 3-8-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Stephanie Phillips had 18 saves for Fullerton, which lost to Cypress, 5-0, the 
other time the teams played this season. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire women's games: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 3, Palomar 1 -- Danae Fielder scored consecutive second-half 
goals to give the Pirates (12-5, 9-4) a 2-1 lead. The victory over second-place 
Palomar (10-5-3, 9-3-2) kept OCC in the running for a conference playoff bid. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Valley 3, San Diego Mesa 1 -- Shannon Cunningham, Lindsey Hayward and 
Courtney Leonard each scored for third-place Irvine Valley (10-4-1, 9-3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 4, San Diego City 3 -- Robyn Camarillo and Erica Hills each 
had a goal and an assist for host Rancho Santiago (4-8-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 2, Golden West 0 -- Michael McCabe and Pat Ferry each scored in 
the first half for the host Pirates (8-4-4, 4-3-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 3, Fullerton 0 -- Daniel Buda, Duje Babarovic and Joey Mezza each 
scored for host Cypress (5-5-6, 3-3-3). Fullerton is 6-7-3, 4-4-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Valley 3, Riverside 3 -- John Gerdis, Chris Roselli and Flavio Bernal 
scored goals for host Irvine Valley (8-6-4, 4-4-2). 
</P>
