<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUNLAP NAMED ASSISTANT COACH FOR TITAN MEN'S BASKETBALL TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Dunlap, an assistant coach for the past three years at Quincy University 
in Illinois, has been named an assistant basketball coach on Bob Hawking's 
staff at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Dunlap, 31, was a three-year letterman in basketball at UCLA and a member of 
the 1985 NIT championship team coached by Walt Hazzard. 
</P>
<P>
 Dunlap began his coaching career in 1986 with the junior varsity at North 
Hollywood High, his alma mater. He moved to College of the Canyons in 1988 as 
an assistant with the men's program coached by Lee Smelser. He was head coach 
of the women's program there for three years. Those teams compiled a 44-20 
record. 
