COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE; PEDESTRIAN STRUCK BY TRUCK, KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A pedestrian was struck and killed at Chapman Avenue and Esplanade Street, 
police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez Gomez Gustavo, 38, of Orange was pronounced dead at the scene after a 
truck heading east on Chapman Avenue struck him shortly after 8 p.m. Monday, 
Officer Jerry Burgess said.Witnesses saw Gustavo in the crosswalk before he was 
hit, Burgess said. The truck driver had a green light and was not cited, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second pedestrian fatality in the city in two weeks. Last week, a 
6-year-old boy on his way to school also was struck and killed at a crosswalk. 
Jonathan Nicasio of Orange was accompanied by his mother, Mirna Pena, who was a 
few steps behind him when the accident occurred. THAO HUA 
</P>
