<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TUSTIN; COMPUTER AWARENESS CLASS TO BE OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Tustin Unified School District is offering a free two-hour lecture for 
residents who want to know more about computers. 
</P>
<P>
 The lecture, "Computer Awareness Night for the Technologically Terrorized," 
will be from 7 to 9 p.m. Nov. 16 in the computer lab of the A.G. Currie Middle 
School, 1402 Sycamore Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Topics will include hardware and software definition, choosing a computer, 
understanding computer basics, how to read a computer store advertisement and 
information on the more advanced multimedia technology and Internet. 
</P>
<P>
 A question-and-answer session will follow. 
</P>
<P>
 Brock Wagner, the school district's management and information director, said 
the lecture will help parents who are thinking of buying a computer for 
themselves and their children. 
</P>
<P>
 The lecture is limited to adults. Information: (714) 730-7369. 
</P>
