<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR PLANNING BOARD 
POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is accepting applications for a vacancy on the Planning Commission 
created by the resignation of Cheryle Hodge. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council is scheduled to appoint Hodge's replacement Jan. 3. 
</P>
<P>
 Application forms for city residents are available weekdays from 8 a.m. to 5 
p.m. at City Hall, 32400 Paseo Adelanto. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission meets on the second and fourth Tuesdays of the month. 
</P>
<P>
 Among other things, the panel makes recommendations to the council on changes 
to the city's General Plan and considers development proposals. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 493-1171. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
