<HEADLINE>
<P>
CKE, PARENT OF CARL'S JR., ALTERS ITS MANAGEMENT TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG JOHNSON, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CKE Restaurants Inc. on Tuesday announced a series of management appointments 
designed to "strengthen the company's two principal operating units." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Chairman William P. Foley II, 48, took on the additional post of chief 
executive, a role he assumed on a temporary basis Oct. 18 when Donald E. Doyle 
resigned as president and chief executive officer. 
</P>
<P>
 Daniel D. (Ron) Lane, 59, a member of a Foley-led investment group that late 
last year took a controlling interest in CKE Restaurants, was appointed vice 
chairman. Lane also was tapped for the newly created post of chief executive 
officer of Boston Pacific Inc., a CKE Restaurants unit that is opening Boston 
Chicken franchise restaurants throughout Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 CKE Restaurants also selected Tom Thompson, 44, for the newly created position 
of president of its Carl Karcher Enterprises Inc. unit, which operates 650 
Carl's Jr. restaurants. Thompson, a longtime Carls' Jr. franchisee, was picked 
as chief operating officer of the burger chain in October. 
</P>
<P>
 Kerry W. Coin, 47, chief operating officer of Boston Pacific Inc. was promoted 
to the new position of president of the chicken restaurant unit. 
</P>
<P>
 The management changes are designed to provide "added breadth to our corporate 
and operating unit structures," Foley said. "We now have strong management 
teams in place for both our operating companies, and I am confident that 
together we can build a great future for CKE." 
</P>
<P>
 The management changes announced Tuesday were prompted in part by the 
departure of Doyle, who is now chief operating officer at Hardee's Food Systems 
Inc., based in Raleigh, N.C. Doyle joined CKE Restaurants in late 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 CKE Restaurants shares closed up 12.5 cents at $8.375 in New York Stock 
Exchange trading Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
