ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: DEVICE FOR COONAN'S HIV TEST KIT GETS FDA APPROVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coonan Clinical Laboratories Inc. said Tuesday that the U.S. Food and Drug 
Administration has approved its blood sampling device for use in its proposed 
in-home test for HIV. 
</P>
<P>
 This approval permits the Costa Mesa company to submit the final application 
for the remainder of the test kit, called HIV-1 Home Check. 
</P>
<P>
 The kit, which would be available over the counter or through the mail if it 
is approved, would allow purchasers to collect a dried blood sample at home. A 
laboratory analysis of the sample would be performed anonymously by mail. 
</P>
