<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Discovision Associates: The company said Tuesday that it has filed a patent 
infringement suit against Technicolor Videocassettes Inc. for three violations 
of U.S. patent law. 
</P>
<P>
 Discovision, an Irvine research firm that developed several technologies used 
in producing optically read discs, said the Camarillo-based subsidiary of 
Technicolor is using its patented technology to create compact discs and has 
repeatedly refused to enter into licensing agreements. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokesman for Technicolor denied any wrongdoing. "It is our policy to comply 
with all valid patents," said Dave Eliot. The lawsuit, filed Friday in U.S. 
District Court in Delaware, seeks damages and an injunction against further 
infringement by TVI. 
