<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I-Flow Corp.: The company said Tuesday that it has signed an agreement with 
Oncology Therapeutics Network to market and distribute I-Flow's reusable IV 
infusion system, designed for the delivery of chemotherapy drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 Oncology Therapeutics, based in San Francisco, distributes drugs and supplies 
to 1,800 of the estimated 2,200 oncology practices nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine-based manufacturer of infusion systems estimates that it will earn 
$250,000 for the last quarter of 1994 as a result of the new agreement. 
</P>
