<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A gala dinner honoring renowned ceramic artist Beatrice Wood and benefiting 
the Archives of American Art will be held Saturday night at the Surf and Sand 
Hotel, 1555 S. Coast Highway, Laguna Beach. Wood, who recently celebrated her 
101st birthday, has lived and worked in Ojai for nearly 50 years.Information: 
(714) 588-2217. 
</P>
<P>
 Privately founded in 1954, the Archives of American Art became a bureau of the 
Smithsonian Institution in 1970. The archives collects, preserves and makes 
available for study more than 12 million documents: the records, original 
papers, photographs, diaries and oral histories of artists, craftsmen, 
collectors, dealers, critics and museums. Federal funding through the 
Smithsonian accounts for 35% of the archives' operating budget; the rest comes 
from individual and corporate gifts. 
</P>
<P>
 Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</TEXT>
